According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Oral Health Care Market was valued at USD 14.3 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 14.8 billion in 2026 to USD 19.9 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 3.8% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth due to rising consumer awareness regarding preventive dental care, increasing demand for premium oral hygiene products, and continuous innovation in smart oral care technologies. Growing emphasis on sustainable formulations and natural ingredients is also reshaping product development across Europe.
The growing focus on preventive healthcare and oral hygiene has significantly increased the adoption of advanced oral care products, including electric toothbrushes, therapeutic toothpaste, mouthwash, whitening solutions, and specialized treatments for gum disease and tooth sensitivity. Public health campaigns, higher healthcare awareness, and expanding access to professional dental care continue to encourage consumers to invest in daily oral hygiene routines.
